  "texts": [
    "This section briefly discusses aggregation-guided BERT-based approaches as a subclass of BERT-based models for integrating semantic information, while the previous section (Section 3.2) considered aggregation-guided methods and block selection models for handling long documents.• Sentence-level score aggregation: The state-of-the-art [132,144] approaches of this sort divide the document into a set of sentences, where the final document score is a linear aggregation of the top k scores retrieved by BERT and the original document score retrieved by the traditional model.",
    "Yang et al. [132] used the sentence-level model to apply BERT to document retrieval and divided the document into a set of sentences by combining the BERT score with the BM25 (Anserini [94]) score to obtain the final score of document retrieval.",
    "Specifically, the final document score was a linear aggregation of the top k scores retrieved by BERT and the original document score retrieved by the traditional model.",
    "Yilmaz et al. [132] proposed a system called 𝐵𝑖𝑟𝑐ℎ [144], which is similar to the proposal in [132], that is shown in Figure 4.",
    "Both these studies ( [144], [132]) reported experiments on two datasets: the TREC 2011-2014 Microblog and Robust04."
  ],
